> Seasoned with honey and fiery, flavorful harissa powder, our sweet and spicy BBQ sauce elevates tender pork chops to new heights. The succulent chops are served with garlicky rice tossed with zucchini and black beans that soak up all the extra flavor. With a sprinkling of fresh scallions over top, this hearty meal is one you'll keep coming back for!

== Garlicky Rice ==

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Add @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Zucchini & Black Beans ==

While rice cooks, trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick pieces.

Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and season with salt and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Pork ==

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @harissa powder{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. (Be sure to measure the harissa powder—we sent more!)

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest at least ~{3%minutes}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

== Honey BBQ Glaze ==

While pork cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, 1 TBSP water, @harissa powder{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, a pinch of salt, and pepper to combine (2 TBSP water, 2 tsp harissa powder, and 1/2 tsp sugar for 4 servings). (Save remaining harissa powder for another use.)

In pan used for pork, bring honey BBQ mixture and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings) to a simmer over medium heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. (If glaze seems too thick, add more water 1 tsp at a time.)

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in zucchini and beans. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice between plates. Top with pork. Drizzle honey BBQ sauce over pork; top with scallion greens. Serve.